1 MARINE_BASE_WALKTHROUGH~
&BThe following is a walkthrough of the Marine players starting base.  

&CGeneral Equipment:
&YWhen you first enter Alien vs Predator : Legends, if you chose the Marine
class, you will find yourself in a somewhat large and confusing base. To
begin with, lets show you were to find your standard devices such as
lights and grenades. Now, to get to the General Equipment room. Go 1 room
east, then 1 room north. Here you will find your motion tracker, radio,
gps system, grenades, flashlights, and other little tidbits.

&CArmor and Weapons
&YNow, from there, to get your armor, You go south 1 room, the east 1, then
1 room north. Here you will find the armor available to Marines. Each
piece of armor gives a diffrent amount of protection in different fields.
To find your standard light weapons, pistols, pulse rifle, etc, You will
need to go south 1, then east 1. Here you find your light guns. To find
your heavier guns, like the Sniper rifles, Shotguns, and the Minigun, you
can go west 1, then south 1.

&CMedical Supplies
&YFor your skills such as Basic and Advanced Medical, you will need to pay
a visit to the MEdical wing of the base. To get there, you will need to
return to the spawn room. Remember the first room you saw? Just retrace
your steps to get back. Now, to get to the medical wing, we will need to
go 2 rooms to the north and 3 rooms to the west.  Here you can buy
painkillers, which heal you somewhat, but will degrade if not used, and
you can get the Bandages needed for Basic Medical, and the Medical Kits
used for Advanced Medical.

&GLeaving the base and Entering the Combat
&RWhen leaving the base and entering the combat arena, its a good thing to
look at the TIME to see if you will need a flashlight or not. If the time
is after 6AM and before 7PM, then its daylight, and you don't need a
flashlight immediatly. To get to the DEPLOYment zone, you need to return to
the central room, the first room you were in, and you will need to go
SOUTH twice, then east, and possibly open the south door. Otherwise, go
south, then west. To leave the base and finally enter the arena, use the
DEPLOY command to see your available DEPLOYment zones. Just use DEPLOY <#>
to enter the field. You can return at anytime by returning to the room you
deployed to and using the DEPLOY command again.
~

