1 YAUTJA PREDATOR~
&CYautja are a Nomadic, Matriarch society. For the most part they live
aboard ships, in packs. Packs are bands, of generally all males who may
stay together for a single hunt, or for years.

Yautja live to hunt, to claim torphies of what they consider worthy prey.
There have been few instances where 'worthy prey' who have slain Yautja
were deemed honorable enough to be left alone. A rare case, and only seen
from Elder Predators. Usually then are just seen as a better trophy, should
be best another Yautja hunter. Yautja hunt other Predators, to kill the
killer. His tropies become your own, a true accomplishment. This is their
interest in Kainde Amedha (Aliens).

Yautja exist in a primarily Matriarchal society. While the males are
generally nomadic, living aboard their ships, and carrying their
possesions, females claim territory, and generally run the politics of the
Yautja society. It's rare, but not unheard of to see a female warrior. It's
also worth noting, that Yautja females are considerably larger than the
males. The males are rarely shorter than seven foot tall.

&RContinued in: &GPredator2, and Yautja2
~

1 YAUTJA2 PREDATOR2~
Yautja are governed stricly by a caste system. The strongest rule, and
number of trophies is a measure of strength. This caste system effects
living areas aboard ships. Young warriors usually live in the lower decks,
sleeping where they can fit themselves, while elder Yautja who have earned
their place are offered more luxurious accommdations. This is also how
ownership, or command of a ship is issued per pack. Yautja vessels stay in
service for centuries, and over time gain unique appearances between the
various packs roaming their hunting grounds. 

Weapons, the Yautja have engage someone in hand to hand combat. have
several melee weapons, and thrown weapons. The naginata and combi-spear
being a few of the more popular melee weapons. Smart discs, spearguns, and
plasma casters make up the main stay of the Predator armorment. Although
there are many other weapons reserved for a time of war. Armor is
similiar, although quite durable, it is usually limited to light or medium
armor for ease of mobility.  Heavy armor is reserved for all out war, on a
crowded battlefields or 'bug harvesting'. Predators, capture and use Queen
Aliens to lay eggs.  Which they pack into pods and drop on colonies, or
planets inhabited with creatures capable of being hosts. When someone
comes to investigate, they are infected, and we have an LV-426 situation
on our hands. As soon as someone is infected the pods report it back to
the vessel they were launched from, then it's time to begin to the hunt.
~

